Preliminary Results Preliminary results indicate that coverage calculations are prone to manipulation since developers alter it with the nocov tags in comments. Source code comments indicate the introduction of &ldquo;Build Debt&rdquo;, followed by &ldquo;Code&rdquo; and &ldquo;Defect Debt&rdquo;, with checks related to &ldquo;R Code Quality&rdquo; being the most exposed.
In StackOverflow, checks about &ldquo;Description&rdquo;, &ldquo;R Code&rdquo;, and &ldquo;Package Structure&rdquo; are the most queried, with about a third of enquiries resulting in an avoidance behaviour. Moreover, there was a peak of enquiries of any type during 2020.

